28/09/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Media reported on Monday (September 27th) that Montenegro and Serbia have agreed on the terms of an agreement to extradite people suspected of a handful of specific crimes. It was reached during a meeting Friday in Podgorica between teams from the two justice ministries. The agreement would allow Montenegro and Serbia to mutually extradite those suspected of organised crime, crimes against humanity, corruption or money laundering. (Beta, RTCG, B92, FoNet - 27/09/10)
